# Memories

- Toggle whole site sections in `src/data/site.yaml` (`sections.projects`, `sections.tldrs`, `sections.caseStudies`). When false, nav links and pages for that section are hidden.
- Dokploy/Nixpacks deploy uses `npm ci --omit=dev` (not bun). Set `NIXPACKS=1` at build time; enable Dokploy build cache for faster redeploys.
- Card grids (`.card-grid` in `global.css`) use `auto-fill` (not `auto-fit`) so a single card stays one column wide instead of stretching full width. Blog/case-study index grids (`#filtered-posts`, `#filtered-case-studies`) share a `repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr))` rule.
- Image blog/case-study cards need `.blog-cards-with-video .blog-card.blog-card--has-image` (not bare `.blog-card--has-image`) to override the square `aspect-ratio: 1` and padding from `.blog-cards-with-video .blog-card`.
- Use `bun run compress-video` for MP4 compression; DaVinci `apv1` exports are not decodable by system `ffmpeg`, so export H.264/HEVC/ProRes first.
- Astro `security.allowedDomains`: set `SITE_URL` at Nixpacks build time; use separate `{ protocol }` and `{ hostname }` entries (not combined) so `X-Forwarded-Proto` validation works behind Cloudflare/Dokploy.
- Project cards show a 30-day commit heatmap (not milestone %). Fetch via `getCommitActivity` in `src/lib/github.ts`; cache key `commits30d:{owner/repo}` in `.cache/github.json`. Use cache in prod (1h TTL); home/projects index are prerendered so GitHub isn't hit on every request.
- Astro `<script define:vars>` becomes an inline script — ESM imports silently break in the browser. Use a normal bundled `<script>` and pass data via DOM/data attributes instead.
- Modern Chrome hides closed `<details>` content via `::details-content { content-visibility: hidden }` — CSS `display` overrides on the child no longer reveal it. The TOC (`PostToc.astro`) ships `<details open>`; `TocScrollSpy` collapses it on mobile (`max-width: 900px`) and reopens on resize to desktop. Mobile ToC overlay: collapse `.post-toc-disclosure::details-content { block-size: 0; overflow: visible }` and position the open panel on `::details-content` (not just the list) so the open slot doesn't reserve layout height and push body content down.
- `/projects` filtering hides/shows the server-rendered cards by `data-slug` (no client-side HTML re-rendering). Heatmap hover is one delegated document listener in `src/components/ui/CommitHeatmap.astro` that swaps the `.commit-heatmap-caption` text; no per-box tooltips (they got clipped by the card's `overflow: hidden`). Project cards use a full-card overlay link (`z-index: 0`) with `.project-content { z-index: 1; pointer-events: none }` so clicks pass through to the link; heatmap and `.tag-clickable` use `pointer-events: auto` for hover/filter interactivity.
- Easter egg: type `awesome` while not focused on an input/textarea/select/contenteditable to toggle slow RGB cycling on accent colors. JS in `src/lib/easter-eggs.ts` drives inline `--accent`/`--accent-soft`/`--accent-deep` from one shared hue per element (chip bg + text stay matched); sections/cards stagger by document position + time via rAF. State persists in `sessionStorage` (`portfolio:accent-rgb-cycle`). Disabled when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.
- Default social/Discord embed card is a static `public/og-image.png` (1200x630), regenerated with `node scripts/generate-og-image.mjs` (uses `sharp` to rasterize a hand-built SVG matching brand colors/logo). Requires Inter TTFs installed as system fonts (`~/.fonts` + `fc-cache -f`) for correct text rendering — the sandbox had no Inter font by default, downloaded from `github.com/rsms/inter` releases. `Layout.astro` falls back to this image (as an absolute URL via `Astro.site`) when no per-page `image` prop is given; only adds `og:image:width/height` meta when using this default (per-page images may differ in aspect ratio).
- Home page code typing (`HomeCodeTyping.astro`): JS-created lines need `<style is:global>`. Leading indent via inline `padding-left: Nch` (4ch per tab). Viewport-aligned horizontal `mask-image` fade toward content column; typing stops (no reset) when file ends or bottom is reached. Mobile uses `0.62rem` (~10px) — set `-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%` on `.home-code-typing` or Safari iOS auto-inflates inline token spans after load (~jumps to ~0.82rem). Width is viewport-capped (`calc(100vw - gutters)`) so long typed lines don't widen the page.
- `html, body, main.container { overflow-x: clip; }` prevents mobile side-to-side page scroll. Card grids use `minmax(min(100%, Npx), 1fr)` so columns don't exceed narrow viewports.
- Post/project hero banners (`.post-hero-banner`) must not use `100vw` for width — iOS Safari treats vw wider than the visible viewport, and centering a vw-sized banner on the narrower article column widens `scrollWidth`. Cap with `min(..., calc(100% + 2rem))` to match container margins; on mobile use full article width (no spill/centering). Clip decorative overflow on `.post--has-banner` and `.post-content`. Banner lives inside `.post-hero` (not the article root); on mobile size it with `height: 100%` so it matches the hero text block instead of a fixed `52vh` slab that leaves empty space above the ToC.
